---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Kingdom Farm"
	description="Regenerative farming for food independence. Clean food shouldn’t be a privilege."
>
	<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 md:py-24">
		<!-- Hero -->
		<div class="text-center mb-16 md:mb-20">
			<div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl bg-primary/10 text-primary mb-6">
				<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
					<path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 2a2 2 0 00-2 2v11a3 3 0 106 0V4a2 2 0 00-2-2H4zm1 14a1 1 0 100-2 1 1 0 000 2zm5-1.757l4.9-4.9a2 2 0 000-2.828L13.485 5.1a2 2 0 00-2.828 0L10 5.757v8.486zM16 18H9.071l6-6H16a2 2 0 012 2v2a2 2 0 01-2 2z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
				</svg>
			</div>
			<h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">Kingdom Farm</h1>
			<p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-base-content/70 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-tight">
				Regenerative farming for food independence.<br class="hidden md:block" />
				Clean food shouldn’t be a privilege.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- The Vision -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-16">
			<h2>The vision</h2>
			<p>
				We’re a family of six building a regenerative farm — not as a hobby, but as a response to a problem we live every month: 
				paying $2,000–$3,000 just to feed our kids clean, nutritious food. That’s rent money in most places. 
				Most families can’t do it.
			</p>
			<p>
				We’re studying pasture-based, regenerative models popularized by farmers like Joel Salatin — rotational grazing, 
				healthy soil, animals raised with respect, and direct-to-family food systems. Our plan is to run an ad-hoc CSA 
				with simple recipes so families who can’t normally afford organic can eat well. Long-term, we hope to help encourage 
				and equip other small farmers so more communities can move toward real food independence.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Why This Matters -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-16">
			<h2>Why this matters</h2>
			<p>
				Clean, nutritious food should not be a privilege. It should be normal. When families can’t afford it, 
				their health, energy, and future pay the price. We’ve felt that strain ourselves.
			</p>
			<p>
				We believe a well-run regenerative farm can do more than grow food. It can grow hope. It can restore dignity. 
				It can show people that someone cares about their bodies and their tables — not just their wallets.
			</p>
			<p class="font-medium">
				That’s the kind of place we want to build. One that feels like Jesus loving people on earth through dirt, sweat, 
				and good food.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- What We Hope to Build -->
		<div class="mb-16">
			<h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold mb-6">What we hope to build</h2>
			
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-base-300 p-6">
					<div class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">A regenerative farm</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">
						Pasture-based systems that build soil, produce real food, and treat animals and land with dignity.
					</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-base-300 p-6">
					<div class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">An ad-hoc CSA with recipes</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">
						Weekly or bi-weekly shares for families who want clean food but can’t normally afford it — plus simple, 
						practical recipes so the food actually gets used and enjoyed.
					</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-base-300 p-6">
					<div class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Seeding other farmers (long-term)</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">
						We hope to help encourage and equip other small farmers so more communities can move toward real food independence.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Where We Are Right Now -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-16">
			<h2>Where we are right now</h2>
			<p>
				We’ve been full-time RVing with our four kids (ages 4, 7, 10, and 12) for over two and a half years. 
				I work full-time as a senior software engineer. We’re currently traveling in the RV while scouting land 
				in and around the Floyd County area of Georgia.
			</p>
			<p>
				We don’t have the farm yet. We have a clear direction, a growing conviction, and a willingness to do the slow, 
				honest work of figuring this out in public. We’re sharing as much as we can honestly and wisely.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- What This Is Not (NEW) -->
		<div class="mb-16 rounded-3xl bg-base-200 p-8 md:p-10">
			<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">What this is not</h2>
			
			<div class="max-w-md mx-auto space-y-4 text-base-content/80">
				<p><strong>Kingdom Farm is not</strong> a polished success story yet.</p>
				<p><strong>It is not</strong> a fundraiser disguised as a blog.</p>
				<p><strong>It is not</strong> a promise that we have all the answers.</p>
				
				<p class="pt-2 font-medium text-base-content">
					It is a family learning in public, counting the cost, and trying to build something useful and faithful.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- What We’re Learning -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-16">
			<h2>What we’re learning along the way</h2>
			<p>
				Every month we’re learning about soil, grazing, costs, business models, and what it actually takes to make 
				this kind of food accessible instead of elite. We’re also learning about ourselves — what we’re willing to 
				give up, what we’re not, and how to keep hope alive when progress feels slow.
			</p>
			<p class="font-medium">
				This isn’t a highlight reel. It’s the real, messy, hopeful path.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- How to Follow -->
		<div class="mb-16 rounded-3xl bg-base-200 p-10 text-center">
			<h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold mb-4">How to follow the journey</h2>
			<p class="max-w-md mx-auto mb-8 text-base-content/80">
				The best way to stay with us is through honest monthly updates — land search stories, research, cost breakdowns, 
				lessons learned, and the quiet prayers that shape the vision.
			</p>
			
			<div class="max-w-xs mx-auto">
				<a href="/newsletter" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg w-full">
					Follow the Kingdom Farm journey
				</a>
				<p class="text-xs text-base-content/60 mt-3">Monthly updates • Real talk • No spam</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Ways to Help -->
		<div class="mb-16">
			<h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-4">Ways to help right now</h2>
			<p class="text-center text-base-content/70 max-w-md mx-auto mb-8">
				Not everyone can give money. That’s okay. Here’s what would actually move the mission forward today:
			</p>

			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-base-300 p-6">
					<div class="font-semibold mb-2">Share the vision</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">If this mission resonates, tell people who care about food, farming, or helping families.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-base-300 p-6">
					<div class="font-semibold mb-2">Offer advice or expertise</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">We’re still learning. If you know regenerative farming, soil, business setup, or land in north Georgia — we’d love your input.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-base-300 p-6">
					<div class="font-semibold mb-2">Supplies or labor (later)</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">Once we have land, help with fencing, tools, or hands-on work will be huge.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-2xl border border-base-300 p-6">
					<div class="font-semibold mb-2">Pray with us</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/80">This is a faith-shaped mission. Your prayers matter more than you know.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Kingdom Farm Builders (Soft) -->
		<div class="border-t pt-12">
			<div class="max-w-xl mx-auto text-center">
				<h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Kingdom Farm Builders</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-base-content/80 mb-6">
					Some of you have asked how you can support the mission financially. We’re grateful.
				</p>
				<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-8">
					We’re not launching a formal support program yet. Right now the most important thing is building trust 
					through honest updates and real progress. When the time comes, we’ll invite a small group of early Builders 
					to help fund specific milestones — and we’ll be transparent about how every dollar is used. 
					You’ll be the first to know.
				</p>
				
				<a href="/newsletter" class="btn btn-outline">
					Stay in the loop
				</a>
				
				<p class="mt-8 text-xs text-base-content/60 max-w-sm mx-auto">
					Kingdom Farm is a family mission in progress. We’re committed to being honest about where we are, 
					where we’re going, and what it actually takes.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>